<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1929,2026]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="514" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[284,424,1929,1954]" class="Gastropoda" family="Diaphanidae" genus="Colpodaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[284,424,1929,1954]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">Colpodaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<typeStatus box="[498,546,1930,1954]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName box="[651,764,1929,1954]" class="Gastropoda" family="Diaphanidae" genus="Colpodaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis box="[651,764,1929,1954]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">C. pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was introduced by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sars" box="[1004,1186,1930,1954]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" refString="Sars, M. (1870) Bidrag til Kundskab om Christianiafjordens fauna. II. Nyt Magazin for Naturvidenkaberne, 172 - 225." type="book chapter" year="1870">
M. Sars (
<number box="[1117,1178,1930,1954]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" value="1870.0">1870</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Later 
<bibRefCitation author="Brown" box="[1273,1436,1930,1954]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" refString="Brown, G. H. (1979) An investigation of the anatomy of Colpodaspis pusilla (Mollusca: Opisthobranchia) and a description of a new species of Colpodaspis from Tanzanian coastal waters. Journal of Zoology, 187, 201 - 221. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1979. tb 03944. x" type="journal article" year="1979">
Brown (
<number box="[1369,1427,1930,1954]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" value="1979.0">1979</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described a new species 
<taxonomicName box="[425,575,1965,1990]" class="Gastropoda" family="Diaphanidae" genus="Colpodaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="thompsoni">
<emphasis box="[425,575,1965,1990]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">C. thompsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and these are the only representatives of the genus. Both species have a thin internal globose shell with depressed or slightly protruding spire and wide aperture. The head is short with rolled up tentacles and visible eyes. The mantle forms an exhalant siphon. Operculum is absent. The foot is large, anteriorly lobed and possesses a longitudinal median furrow on the sole. The external autospermal tract is ciliated, penial armature is absent.
</paragraph>
